Get ready to elevate a classic chicken salad into an irresistible meal that's packed with flavor, texture, and color. You'll toss together juicy grape tomatoes, peppery arugula, and our hearty mixed grain blend with creamy Dijon vinaigrette, then top with warm oregano-seasoned chicken, Parmesan, and the star of the show: crispy fried prosciutto.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Crispy Prosciutto ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @prosciutto{2%oz} slices in a single layer; sear until browned and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side (you may need to work in batches).

> TIP: Press down on prosciutto with a spatula for even crisping. If prosciutto starts to crisp too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Dressing ==

While prosciutto cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and minced). Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz} (halved).

In a large #bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp sugar and a large drizzle of olive oil.

Stir in shallot; set aside to marinate.

== Grain Blend ==

Massage @microwavable grain blend{1} in package to break up grains; partially open package. Microwave until warmed through, ~{1 1/2-2%minutes}.

Spread grain blend out on a #plate{} to cool.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with paper towels; season all over with @dried oregano{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> Use half the oregano for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for prosciutto over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Assembly ==

While chicken cooks, roughly chop prosciutto.

To bowl with dressing, add tomatoes, grain blend, @arugula{2%oz}, half the prosciutto, and @parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}. Toss to combine.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide salad between #bowls{}. Top with chicken, remaining prosciutto, and remaining Parmesan. Serve.